{"id":14881065,"mediaExerciseId":"87d349ea-feea-46f5-99ff-0c33b2a903fc","exerciseName":"16","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612313,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":234,"solutions":[{"id":6007972,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This task **asks to analyze Figure 7.4.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**a)**\n\nFrom Figure 7.4 we have to find out the coupon rate.\n\nCoupon rates are determined by the entity that issues a bond. The coupon value will be the same for every future payment. So it is a fixed amount. From the Figure, we can see that the coupon rate is **4.50\\%.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":30,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/b0eb48f97f0f26c998291678ff6f08d2/463f06adc857cd7258a97408a1a88c67/lateximg_large.png","width":546},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/b0eb48f97f0f26c998291678ff6f08d2/463f06adc857cd7258a97408a1a88c67/lateximg.png","width":274}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**b)**\n\nBid and ask price we can face on the OTC market or any other dealers markets.\n\nThe bid price shows how much the bond buyer is prepared to pay in order to have security. Ask price shows how much the seller is prepared to sell the security. If we subtract the bid price by the asked price, we will calculate the dealer's profit. \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{bid-ask spread in \\$}&=\\left(\\text{ask price}-\\text{bid price}\\right)\\times\\text{par value}\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\left(128.1520-128.0625\\right)\\times\\$10,000\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\$895\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**The bid-ask spread in $ is $895.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":181,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/b0eb48f97f0f26c998291678ff6f08d2/c9eb01bdf18e0937402061be500eda7f/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/b0eb48f97f0f26c998291678ff6f08d2/c9eb01bdf18e0937402061be500eda7f/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"**c)**\n\nThe previous day asked price we can find by subtracting the value from the change column from the asked price for the current year. \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{previous day asked price}&=\\dfrac{\\text{asked price}_{05/15/2038}-\\text{change}}{100}\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\dfrac{128.1520-0.6875}{100}\\\\[15pt]\n&=1.2746\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThat is the amount that we need to multiply by the par value.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":552,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/b0eb48f97f0f26c998291678ff6f08d2/a30ab54fee35b68585d8c518ebfa6541/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":277,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/b0eb48f97f0f26c998291678ff6f08d2/a30ab54fee35b68585d8c518ebfa6541/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's get the result in dollars.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{previous day asked price}&=1.2746\\times\\$10.000\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\boxed{\\$12,746.45}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**The previous day's asked price is \\$12,746.45.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":458,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/b0eb48f97f0f26c998291678ff6f08d2/cde66769672b61958964316080e908c2/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":229,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/b0eb48f97f0f26c998291678ff6f08d2/cde66769672b61958964316080e908c2/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isRe